verbose_text: After stratification by first-trimester BMI, these increased risks of GDM (OR = 3.54, 95% CI : 1.44-8.72) and elevated fasting (mean difference = 0.39 mmol/L, 95% CI : 0.13-0.65) and 2-h blood (mean difference = 1.24 mmol/L, 95% CI : 0.56-1.91) glucose levels were significant only in the IVF group who is also overweight or obese (BMI> 25 kg/m 2).
